addMark

protected void addMark(com.ibm.eclipse.core.resources.IMarker marker)
Hook to create an internal LPEX text-widget mark for a marker. The implementation of this method does nothing, it must be extended in a subclass to create an LPEX mark corresponding to the marker specified. LPEX keeps its marks up-to-date during editing, but not its IDocument.

createMarker

public com.ibm.eclipse.core.resources.IMarker createMarker(int markerType)
Create a marker of the given type for the editor's input element. The marker is not yet registered with the marker manager.

Use this method to get a new instance of a bookmark, breakpoint, or task. Then, set positional attributes, and use addMarker() to add the marker to the system.

On a related note, LPEX supports a rich marking functionality (element and character marks, either 'sticky' or 'non-sticky', with display style and visibility attributes, etc.). Refer to the LPEX mark parameter and related.

Parameters:
type - type of the new marker (e.g., IMarker.BOOKMARK)
See Also:
addMarker(com.ibm.eclipse.core.resources.IMarker)
